Gun Owners South Africa says crime is escalating, and perpetrators are becoming increasingly violent. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gun Owners South Africa is disputing Gun Safe Cities’ research on gun ownership in South Africa. Gun Safe Cities says possessing a firearm is not a solution. It says research shows that people are more likely to have their gun used against them than being able to use it for self-defence. READ: Teacher suspended for supervising exam with firearm However, Gun Owners South Africa says crime is escalating, and perpetrators are becoming increasingly violent. “There is no research, there is no background to it, Gun Safe Cities is a shill for the gun control lobby,” said chairman of Gun Owners South Africa Paul Oxley. “They’re paid propagandists of foreign interests.” Gosa says it promotes responsible gun ownership.